import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_10_airports = data.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().nlargest(10)
    top_10_airports.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What are the top 10 airports with the highest number of flights?')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xlabel('Airport')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of flights between airports?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_10_routes = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).sum().sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).reset_index().head(10)
    plt.bar(top_10_routes['origin'] + ' to ' + top_10_routes['destination'], top_10_routes['count'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What are the top 10 busiest routes in terms of number of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['count'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['count'], vert=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of flights per airport?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = np.random.randint(100, 1000, data.shape[0])
    plt.scatter(data['count'], data['distance'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of flights and the distance between airports?')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.ylabel('Distance between Airports')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
